    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just to make sure I understand the issue, could you confirm this is the workflow you have in mind?\n1. Users selects a project in a dropdown list (helped with an autocomplete so they do not have to scroll into the whole list).\n2. Results are filtered, so only hits that matches this project are displayed\n3. Users can type a query to further refine the list of results\n\nIn your example, the dropdown is populated through a secondary index, but this is actually used as a list of facets. How many projects (approx.) do you have in this list? Just to see if we're talking about a dropdown on a small list of facets, or a full search in another index.\n\nEdit: Oh I just saw #401 where you've been asked to do a separate index. I guess this answers my question :)\n",
