    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As of today, I think you could be able to build something like this using our [autocomplete.js](https://github.com/algolia/autocomplete.js) library (this is a fork of Typeahead that uses Algolia) and the `instantsearch.helper` property (that maps to our [javascript helper](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js).\n\nThis will require a bit of plumbing, but the main idea would be to listen to the `autocomplete:selected` event of `autocomplete.js`, and here add a new `facetRefinement` to the `helper`, that matches the value selected in `autocomplete`...\n\nWe have plans to add search into facets values directly at the API level, but no ETA at the moment. I don't think we're going to add this feature like this directly into instantsearch core (because of file size, and custom setup requirements in term of indices), but maybe we should write a detailed guide on how our two libraries could work together.\n\nAny other thoughts @redox @vvo @bobylito ?\n",
