  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Here's what I came up with - I am sure there are better ways, but this works.\r\nNote, it is presumed you do add relevant libs on your own, and I use this with Typesense, but it should also work with Algolia since it uses instantsearchJS\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst customMenuSelect = instantsearch.connectors.connectMenu((renderOptions, isFirstRender) => {\r\n            const { refine, items, widgetParams } = renderOptions;\r\n\r\n            if (isFirstRender) {\r\n                const select = document.createElement('select');\r\n                widgetParams.container.appendChild(select);\r\n\r\n                select.addEventListener('change', event => {\r\n                    refine(event.target.value || '');\r\n                });\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            const select = widgetParams.container.querySelector('select');\r\n            select.innerHTML = '';\r\n\r\n            // Add an 'All' option at the top of the select element\r\n            const allOption = document.createElement('option');\r\n            allOption.value = '';\r\n            allOption.text = 'All';  // Adjust this label if needed\r\n            allOption.selected = items.every(item => !item.isRefined);\r\n            select.appendChild(allOption);\r\n\r\n            // Add other options with counts\r\n            items.forEach(item => {\r\n                const option = document.createElement('option');\r\n                option.value = item.value;\r\n                option.text = `${item.label} (${item.count})`;  // Including count here\r\n                option.selected = item.isRefined;\r\n                select.appendChild(option);\r\n            });\r\n\r\n            // Re-initialize Select2 after updating options\r\n            $(select).select2({\r\n                placeholder: 'Select a Category',\r\n                allowClear: true,\r\n                width: '100%',\r\n            }).on('select2:select select2:unselect', function (e) {\r\n                refine(e.target.value || '');\r\n            });\r\n        });\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd in the `addWidgets`:\r\n```\r\n...\r\ncustomMenuSelect({\r\n\t\t\t\t\tcontainer: document.querySelector('#categories-refinement-list'),\r\n\t\t\t\t\tattribute: 'Category'\r\n\t\t\t\t}),\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis does produce a working select2 that is populated with values from the attribute, and updates accordingly when values are changed.",
    "created_at": "2024-09-10T06:22:44Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/757#issuecomment-2339768938",
    "id": 2339768938,
